[{'text': 'Hi, my name is David, otherwise known as The iBook Guy. Let me tell you a little bit about what I do.', 'start': 0.73, 'duration': 5.27}, {'text': "I'm very fond of the first generation iBook, known as the Clamshell, and the second generation known as the Snow iBook.", 'start': 6.64, 'duration': 6.68}, {'text': 'I buy these laptops in huge bulk lots, often with various problems. In my spare time,', 'start': 13.84, 'duration': 4.85}, {'text': 'I repair these computers and get them ready for people to use.', 'start': 18.69, 'duration': 2.759}, {'text': 'Then I resell them on eBay and also in my local part of town using Craigslist.', 'start': 21.689, 'duration': 4.11}, {'text': "Let's look over the basic features of these computers. I'll start with the Clamshells.", 'start': 28.269, 'duration': 3.83}, {'text': 'There are four different colors and three different speeds. eBay sellers are always getting this mixed up and advertising these things wrong.', 'start': 32.32, 'duration': 6.579}, {'text': 'So, let me clear things up a bit.', 'start': 39.399, 'duration': 1.601}, {'text': 'The first Clamshells were the Blueberry and Tangerine.', 'start': 41.0, 'duration': 3.8}, {'text': 'Both units were 300 MHz and do not have FireWire ports. These are the most common ones found on eBay.', 'start': 44.8, 'duration': 6.59}, {'text': 'Next, they came out with a Graphite model at 366 MHz.', 'start': 52.09, 'duration': 3.59}, {'text': 'Next, they introduced the Indigo and the Key Lime units, which were 366 MHz and also added FireWire ports.', 'start': 56.5, 'duration': 6.41}, {'text': 'The last Clamshells made were the Special Edition Graphite and Key Lime models, which had 466 MHz processors.', 'start': 64.51, 'duration': 7.069}, {'text': "These are very rare and hard to find. In fact in all the bulk lots I bought, I've never come across one.", 'start': 72.04, 'duration': 5.779}, {'text': 'The most common mistake I see is eBay sellers confusing the Blueberry and Indigo models.', 'start': 79.0, 'duration': 5.0}, {'text': 'The easiest way to tell the part is to find out if it has a FireWire port, because only the Indigo model has one.', 'start': 84.0, 'duration': 6.21}, {'text': 'After the Clamshell was discontinued, the next iBook is informally known as the Snow iBook.', 'start': 91.9, 'duration': 5.1}, {'text': "There were over 20 versions of this and they're very difficult to tell apart.", 'start': 97.1, 'duration': 3.98}, {'text': 'The first version used a 500 MHz CPU and the last version used a 1.42 GHz CPU.', 'start': 101.1, 'duration': 5.66}, {'text': 'Even though they all look the same, there are considerable differences internally. I typically just deal with the 500 and 600 MHz versions.', 'start': 107.38, 'duration': 7.7}, {'text': 'Besides repairing them, I also upgrade them. Keep in mind these computers are old.', 'start': 119.34, 'duration': 4.66}, {'text': "In fact, without some upgrades they're virtually useless for today's online world.", 'start': 124.0, 'duration': 3.999}, {'text': 'It actually amazes me that I see some of these things being sold on eBay sometimes for hundreds of dollars, without any upgrades at all.', 'start': 128.46, 'duration': 6.47}, {'text': 'Because the seller will use deceptive advertising.', 'start': 135.33, 'duration': 2.119}, {'text': 'They\'ll use words like "Comes with a HUGE 3 GB hard drive for storing all of your music!"', 'start': 138.06, 'duration': 4.88}, {'text': 'But the truth is, a 3 GB hard drive is barely big enough to do a minimal install of the operating system', 'start': 143.34, 'duration': 5.28}, {'text': 'and there will be no space left over for any music or any other applications to be installed.', 'start': 148.62, 'duration': 4.7}, {'text': 'I\'ve also seen phrases like "Upgraded to 128 MB for speedy performance!"', 'start': 153.32, 'duration': 5.68}, {'text': 'Again, the truth is 128 MB is horrible. It can barely boot a modern operating system, much less give speedy performance.', 'start': 159.18, 'duration': 7.58}, {'text': 'So, in order to make these things usable in the modern world, I upgrade the memory, the hard drive, the operating system and I make sure it has an AirPort card.', 'start': 167.84, 'duration': 8.16}, {'text': 'I also give you a working power supply. It is amazing how many eBay auctions are selling these computers without a power supply, which is crazy!', 'start': 176.0, 'duration': 8.0}, {'text': 'Another common scam to look out for are sellers who advertise their iBook as "Wireless Ready", or something to that effect.', 'start': 185.69, 'duration': 6.74}, {'text': 'It makes it sound like it includes the wireless card, but what it really means is that there is NO wireless card included.', 'start': 192.43, 'duration': 6.57}, {'text': "You won't find any of these fraudulent claims at my advertising.", 'start': 199.0, 'duration': 2.97}]

[{'text': 'Kathy Hopkins, University of Maine Cooperative
Extension Educator: Windows present another', 'start': 6.629, 'duration': 1.19}, {'text': 'insulation problem; they lose a lot of heat
through the glass as glass has no insulating', 'start': 7.819, 'duration': 5.101}, {'text': 'value whatsoever. So, there are some things
you can do to help prevent that transfer of', 'start': 12.92, 'duration': 5.9}, {'text': 'heat through the window. One of the cheapest
is to take bubble wrap that you get in something', 'start': 18.82, 'duration': 5.519}, {'text': 'that you buy and cut it to the shape of the
window exactly, spray a little water on the', 'start': 24.339, 'duration': 6.01}, {'text': 'bubble wrap, put the bubbles toward the glass,
and the thin film of water will help the bubble', 'start': 30.349, 'duration': 6.231}, {'text': 'wrap stay on the glass. You could also tape
it along the sides if you wanted. That will', 'start': 36.58, 'duration': 5.07}, {'text': 'present a little more insulating value to
the glass. If you have to see out the window,', 'start': 41.65, 'duration': 5.39}, {'text': 'then bubble wrap is not your best choice,
but if you dont have to see out through', 'start': 47.04, 'duration': 5.2}, {'text': 'the glass, it can provide some insulation
for the glass.', 'start': 52.24, 'duration': 4.91}, {'text': 'Another thing you can do on a window to provide
some insulation is to put a thin film of plastic', 'start': 57.15, 'duration': 5.78}, {'text': 'over top of the window. You can use painters
tape for this because it comes up easily.', 'start': 62.93, 'duration': 5.2}, {'text': 'It will hold during the winter, but then you
can take it off in the spring without having', 'start': 68.13, 'duration': 4.34}, {'text': 'to worry about peeling the paint off your
windows. And so you want to cut the plastic', 'start': 72.47, 'duration': 6.02}, {'text': 'to size, put the plastic on top, put another
piece to seal it on the side and pull that', 'start': 78.49, 'duration': 10.589}, {'text': 'tight. The object is not to have the plastic
flapping in the breeze; you want that tight', 'start': 89.079, 'duration': 6.201}, {'text': 'and then youd add more tape on the bottom
and then youd have a nice indoor plastic', 'start': 95.28, 'duration': 4.659}, {'text': 'storm window that will provide an air space
and prevent that air infiltration through', 'start': 99.939, 'duration': 6.211}, {'text': 'the window. This is also really easy to come
up, so if you needed to have access to the', 'start': 106.15, 'duration': 5.91}, {'text': 'window you could peel that up pretty easily.', 'start': 112.06, 'duration': 4.46}, {'text': 'Another thing you can do is make your own
indoor storm window out of cardboard that', 'start': 116.52, 'duration': 5.139}, {'text': 'you have laying around, or a few other odds
and ends you have in your house. If you take', 'start': 121.659, 'duration': 4.831}, {'text': 'four layers of cardboard and glue them together,
you can make a pretty nice indoor shutter.', 'start': 126.49, 'duration': 5.19}, {'text': 'The first thing to do is measure your window
and get the exact measurements so your shutter', 'start': 131.68, 'duration': 4.24}, {'text': 'will fit and it will fit right in the window.
Glue your cardboard together, layer on layer,', 'start': 135.92, 'duration': 6.1}, {'text': 'then glue a layer of heavy-duty aluminum foil
on top to act as a vapor barrier and a heat', 'start': 142.02, 'duration': 8.03}, {'text': 'reflector and then seal off the edges with
some duct tape. You can make yourself a duct', 'start': 150.05, 'duration': 5.28}, {'text': 'tape handle and then, at the very end, put
a layer of foam insulation right around the', 'start': 155.33, 'duration': 5.86}, {'text': 'edge of your shutter and then, when youre
ready, you can pop it right into your window', 'start': 161.19, 'duration': 5.92}, {'text': 'frame so it sits nice and tight, and youll
have an indoor shutter. You can put this in', 'start': 167.11, 'duration': 8.48}, {'text': 'at night and take it out during the day, and
save yourself some energy.', 'start': 175.59, 'duration': 5.02}, {'text': 'If youve gone through your house and determined
that your windows are providing a lot of air', 'start': 180.61, 'duration': 5.68}, {'text': 'leakage, there are some simple things you
can do that can make a difference. One is', 'start': 186.29, 'duration': 3.95}, {'text': 'lock your window. Just the simple fact of
locking it brings this sash down and pushes', 'start': 190.24, 'duration': 5.54}, {'text': 'the top sash up and seals it tighter in its
frame, so that can help as well. The other', 'start': 195.78, 'duration': 6.19}, {'text': 'thing is if you dont have curtains or you
havent made these interior shutters yet,', 'start': 201.97, 'duration': 6.18}, {'text': 'even pulling your shade will help at night.
It would be even better if you could seal', 'start': 208.15, 'duration': 7.54}, {'text': 'the sides of the shade down once youve
got them down there. Sometimes you can do', 'start': 215.69, 'duration': 3.49}, {'text': 'that with magnetic strips and put a little
